I'm learning C but my hello world program won't compile. I've included the standard library. Here's my code:

int main (void) {
                            printf("Hello, World")
                            return 0;
                        }

C expects a semicolon before your return statement. Try fixing it with this:

int main (void) {
                            printf("Hello, World");
                            return 0;
                        }
